The paper deals with natural language processing (NLP) and specifically focuses on stance classification, which is a subfield of NLP. Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also uses neural network models, which are commonly used in machine learning and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper leverages BERT representations, which is a popular language model in NLP and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also deals with analyzing online media and discussion forums, which falls under information retrieval (cs.IR) and social and information networks (cs.SI).
